Yesterday as part of our Modern Love series we published a story about 11 of the worst things black women have heard when they were dating white people. The resonated with our readers and since it was published women have been sending us their stories. This is what they had to say.  That's what they taught us in apartheid. Do you really want to take us back there?  Do you ask heterosexual people how they make it work with people of the opposite sex?  Well, if they believe in marriage, then it's not an unbelievable concept.  Unless I have a secret twin, none of his exes could ever look like me.  Lol! Yes, let's take all white people on enlightenment trips so they'll start dating black women.  "I grabbed the first good boy I could find and when the lights went on - gasp - he was white. My bad."  Slow down there, when did our parents get involved?  February is the month of love. At the Huffington Post South Africa, we take a look at how South Africans are finding and holding on to love. Author Shubnum Khan tells us about how cross-border romances are made or broken, tech journalist Nafisa Akabor looks at how social media replaced your meet-cute and lifestyle editor Sarah Koopman has some advice on how to get away from that tired old dinner-and-a-movie setup. Find them all and more here, or try these.